            # Link the created resources to the policies
            link_resources_to_policy(policy['id'], [resource_id])

            _log.info(f"Policy {policy_name} created and resource {resource} linked successfully.")
    except Exception as error:
        raise Exception(f"Error while creating policy and linking resources: {str(error)}")


Why These Changes?:
These changes link the created resources to the relevant policies, ensuring that the policies control access to actual resources.
Minimal changes: We're simply adding the linking logic to connect resources to policies.





3. Fetching RODAN Resources and Presenting in Asset Store
The RODAN resources will be fetched via the entitlements.get_entitlements() function, which queries RODAN for entitlements based on the resource and action filter.
These resources will be grouped and created in the PlainID Asset Store using the create_resource_type and create_resource functions.
Finally, the resources will be linked to policies that govern access to them.


Add Logging to Track Resource Fetching in policies.py:
